{"source_key":"sha256-364390994d45a450aa62c8b6d3ca2577","record_index":1077,"record_hash":"sha256:c7879f9b41c18b7445cbc98ed7fa9419d5db8414ae8f70abd11e24803be92a1a","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:05.198Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12): Drop the new re-export for now. `find_related_sessions`, `RelatedTarget`, `RelatedSession`, `Confidence`, and `AssociationReason` are only used inside `gitmeta.rs` tests. Keep them `pub(crate)` or private until a real external caller lands.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:165](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:165): `RelatedSession` is over-shaped for the first slice. `turn_keys` duplicates `reasons[*].turn_key`, `confidence` is derivable from `score`, and `scoring_version` is static metadata. I’d keep `session_key`, `score`, and one evidence list. The rest is API ballast.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:139](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:139): `AssociationReason::{ObservedBranch, ObservedReview, ObservedChange}` repeats the queried target key on every reason. Since `find_related_sessions(repo, target)` already knows the target, this can collapse to turn evidence, probably just `Vec<String>` turn keys for now.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:90](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:90): `StoredIndexHit` is a duplicate of `IndexHit` with owned strings. Merge them or deserialize the same shape directly; two structs for one JSON object is not earning its keep.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:120](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:120): `observed_targets_field()` exists only to support dynamic JSON indexing. Fine mechanically, but if `AssociationReason` collapses, `RelatedTarget` can probably just expose `kind()` and `key()`, cutting one fake-extension helper.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1167](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1167): The scoring test is doing too much: initial scoring for 3 target kinds, incremental scoring, reason shape, and session fields. Shrink it to score/order/count behavior. The detailed reason assertions mostly lock in the bulky API above.\\n\\n- [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1177](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1177) and [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1285](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:1285): New tests repeat the same session/source/target/batch/environment setup. A tiny helper that writes one observed turn would delete a lot of noise without adding abstraction drama.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:05.198Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}